article.headline: Stetson 81, North Florida 77 (OT)
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon and Anthony Register each scored 19 points to lead Stetson to an 81-77 win over North Florida on Friday night. North Florida (6-20, 3-15) started with a 37-32 lead at the end of the first half. Stetson (10-17, 8-9) outscored North Florida 31-26 in the second half to tie. Stetson kept its momentum, outscoring North Florida 18-14 in overtime. Besides Gordon and Register, Stetson's Gabe McMillen scored 13 points, and Garfield Blair scored 10. North Florida's Alain Laroche, who was the lead scorer for the game, had 21 points. He also had 12 rebounds. Rashad Williams scored 17 points for the team, and Ryan Daugherty scored 11.
